    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="549"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1988</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-10T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.35 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4151. My 3569, April 10, 6 p.m., and Department’s 3673, April 23, 5 p.m.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d549fn1">Not printed; both referred to interference with
                        Russian Ambassador’s cables.</note> Russian Ambassador here is informed by
                    French postal <pb facs="0634" n="560" xml:id="pg_560"/> authorities that his
                    cipher telegram sent June 6 addressed Ambarusse, Washington, has been stopped by
                    American censor. Please investigate and inform me what answer I am to make
                    him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
